b'These mashed potatoes are so good, you'll have even the pickiest eater saying, "More please!" Bonus: they're easy to make and require few ingredients. :down_arrow_selector:

Ingredients:
5 pounds (2.27 kg) potatoes (russet, Yukon gold, red, or a mix!)
2 large cloves garlic, minced
fine sea salt
6 tablespoons (15 ml) butter\xe2\x80\x8b, melted
1 cup (0.24 l) whole milk, or milk of your choice
4 ounces (0.12 l) cream cheese, room temperature
Toppings! :face_savoring_food:

Cooking Instructions:
Step 1
Cut and boil the potatoes. With or without skins, your potatoes should be cut evenly in about one-inch chunks. Transfer to a pot of cold water, then heat on high until boiling. Once boiling, cook for 10-12 minutes. Drain carefully. 

Step 2
Heat the butter, milk and an additional 2 teaspoons of sea salt together either in a small saucepan or in the microwave until the butter is just melted.

Step 3
Mash the potatoes to your desired consistency. Add half the butter mixture and fold it into the potatoes. Repeat with the remaining butter, then again with the cream cheese. Serve warm with your favorite toppings.'
